With COVID-19 cases increasing in Gauteng, there are growing calls for tighter lockdown measures. The SA Medical Research Council says tougher measures on alcohol sales may be necessary. Maurice Smithers, director of South Africa's division of the South African Alcohol Policy Alliance speaks to #eNCA. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There are growing calls for Gauteng to reconsider alcohol sales. Industry expert Maurice Smithers says the government missed the mark on liquor restrictions when it moved the country to alert Level 3 lockdown. READ: SAMRC: Further alcohol sale restrictions may be necessary for Gauteng According to Smithers, from the Southern African Alcohol Policy Alliance, a situation is brewing, particularly at on-sight consumption outlets.